---
description: Organize requires and dependency grouping
alwaysApply: true
---

Split top-of-file dependency declarations into groups in this order:

1) Roblox services
2) Types
3) Constants
4) Helpers
5) My services / controllers / shared systems
6) Classes

Whitespace and placement rules:
- Use exactly one blank line between different groups.
- Do not use blank lines inside the same group.
- Keep each group contiguous.
- Keep dependency groups before non-dependency declarations (for example, type declarations and runtime locals).

Pathing rules:
- You can require scripts that are children using relative `:WaitForChild(...)`.
- Do not navigate upwards for require paths (`script.Parent`, `script.parent`, `Parent.Parent`, etc.).

If anything does not clearly fit one of these categories, ask the user before deciding.
